    },
    {
      "id": "46f1dc84dfb9593c88039e71efd58d54c2dd97bd",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 2,
        "name": "Jenkins",
        "username": "hudson",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-10-10 15:44:20.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Fails\n\nBuild Failed \n \nhttp://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-reviews/18726/ : FAILURE",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "7841e6c8ede15943dbb9968a94bbf45602fb595b",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-10-10 20:19:26.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nThis failed on SLES11 (3.0+) builds with:\n\n context_lucid.c: In function 'derive_key_lucid':\n context_lucid.c:354: error: call to function 'krb5_derive_key' without a real prototype\n context.h:46: note: 'krb5_derive_key' was declared here",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "84fc48ad60977169322050ca3670931fede2dcdf",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-10-10 20:19:37.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "5e8dd570fd56d03a3449d362da29a0e9f4c03807",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 145,
        "name": "Ken Hornstein",
        "email": "kenh@cmf.nrl.navy.mil",
        "username": "kenh"
      },
      "date": "2013-10-11 19:06:41.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nSo I dug into this a bit more.\n\nIt turns out there was generally no prototype for krb5_derive_key() in a public header file; it was a library export, but normally not considered a public function (that's why it was changed to krb5int_derive_key(), which is also exported but apparently has a normal prototype).\n\nI think the only way to correctly resolve this is to put a proper prototype in context.h for krb5_derive_key().",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "5b91f14ddacc25d86f142367754d517df4d09981",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 281,
        "name": "Thomas Stibor",
        "email": "thomas@stibor.net",
        "username": "thomas"
      },
      "date": "2013-10-11 22:36:12.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nThe intention of this patch is to fix the problem, that\n\nchecking for krb5int_derive_key in -lgssapi_krb5... yes\nor\nchecking for krb5_derive_key in -lgssapi_krb5... yes\n\nhowever due to testing non-existing shell variables in kerberos5.m4, it results in\n\nconfigure: WARNING: Disable gss/krb5 due to missing both krb5int_derive_key and krb5_derive_key functions!\n\nThis patch however revealed that the old former function\ncall krb5_derive_key needs proper prototyping:\n\ncontext_lucid.c: In function 'derive_key_lucid':\ncontext_lucid.c:354: error: call to function 'krb5_derive_key' without a real prototype\ncontext.h:46: note: 'krb5_derive_key' was declared here\nmake[5]: *** [lsvcgssd-context_lucid.o] Error 1\nmake[4]: *** [all-recursive] Error 1\nmake[3]: *** [all-recursive] Error 1\nmake[2]: *** [all-recursive] Error 1\nmake[1]: *** [all-recursive] Error 1\n\nWith the current version of kerberos5.m4 the problem can not be caught as GSS is deactivated.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "e1147dd18cc4e183092a95333a15e8cf119b526d",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 281,
        "name": "Thomas Stibor",
        "email": "thomas@stibor.net",
        "username": "thomas"
      },
      "date": "2013-10-11 23:01:16.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nThe approach in context.h\n\n#if HAVE_KRB5INT_DERIVE_KEY\nextern int krb5int_derive_key();\nextern int krb5_k_create_key();\n#else /* !HAVE_KRB5INT_DERIVE_KEY */\nextern int krb5_derive_key();\n#endif\n\nis actually a hack which existed before in code to obtain access to not exported functions.\n\n/usr/include/mit-krb5>grep -r krb5int_derive_key => \"\"\nstrings /usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/libkrb5.so | grep krb5int_derive_key => \"\"\n\nThats why the function is exported this way.\n\nThere is unfortunately a flaw in the autoconf tool.\nThe statement AC_CHECK_LIB($gssapi_lib, krb5int_derive_key\nsuggests that krb5int_derive_key can be accessed via \n\nstrings /usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/libgssapi_krb5.so | grep krb5int_derive_key => \"\"\n\nhowever, that is not the case. It works however, for\ne.g. AC_CHECK_LIB($gssapi_lib, krb5_get_error_message\n\nstrings /usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/libgssapi_krb5.so | grep krb5_get_error_message => \"krb5_get_error_message\"\n\nRegarding the function name, the function name krb5_derive_key was renamed in MIT-Kerberos >= 1.8.X\n\nBefore it was (<= 1.7.X):\n\n~/tmp/krb/krb5-1.7.2>grep -r \"krb5int_derive_key\"\n~/tmp/krb/krb5-1.7.2>grep -r \"krb5_derive_key\"   \nsrc/lib/crypto/vectors.c:    r = krb5_derive_key (enc, in, out, usage);\n\nand with version >= 1.8.X it changed to:\n~/tmp/krb/krb5-1.8.6>grep -r \"krb5_derive_key\"\ndoc/CHANGES:Rename some lingering krb5_derive_key references.\n\n~/tmp/krb/krb5-1.8.6>grep -r \"krb5int_derive_key\"\nsrc/lib/crypto/crypto_tests/vectors.c:    r = krb5int_derive_key (enc, in, out, usage);",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "60e4622a232f6462dd9af93c28cdf9ababd50c33",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 281,
        "name": "Thomas Stibor",
        "email": "thomas@stibor.net",
        "username": "thomas"
      },
      "date": "2013-10-13 21:24:08.000000000",
      "message": "Uploaded patch set 2.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
