      "date": "2013-10-13 22:19:13.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Fails\n\nBuild Failed \n \nhttp://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-reviews/18774/ : FAILURE",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "bbca1d1bf5f95a514a3b25ad86ed0aae527124f9",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 145,
        "name": "Ken Hornstein",
        "email": "kenh@cmf.nrl.navy.mil",
        "username": "kenh"
      },
      "date": "2013-10-15 18:28:58.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nAccording to Hudson, this build failed because of the lack of a definition for krb5_crypto_iov, which is in struct krb5_enc_provider.\n\nSince those functions only take pointers to struct krb5_enc_provider, maybe it would be simpler to declare\nthem anonymously in context.h?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
