        "parents": [
          {
            "commit": "a0e74aa58234752ec01c7a056af41fcefd2e43b6",
            "subject": "LU-4044 build: fix 'resource leak' errors"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Thomas Stibor",
          "email": "thomas@stibor.net",
          "date": "2013-10-10 13:33:33.000000000",
          "tz": 120
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Oleg Drokin",
          "email": "oleg.drokin@intel.com",
          "date": "2013-11-19 14:00:32.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-4085 build: gss/krb5 is disabled despite functions found",
        "message": "LU-4085 build: gss/krb5 is disabled despite functions found\n\nThe function available check for krb5int_derive_key and\nkrb5_derive_key by means of AC_CHECK_LIB($gssapi_lib,...)\ndoes not set shell variables HAVE_KRB5_DERIVE_KEY,\nHAVE_KRB5INT_DERIVE_KEY so the test\nAS_IF([test \"x$HAVE_KRB5INT_DERIVE_KEY\" = \"x1\"\n-o \"x$HAVE_KRB5_DERIVE_KEY\" = \"x1\"] gives false despite\nthe functions are found. As a side effect this fix\nrevealed that calls with real prototypes are required.\nThus prototypes of krb5_derive_key(...) and\nkrb5int_derive_key(...) are provided, and required\nstructures from krb5-int.h are copied.\n\nSigned-off-by: Thomas Stibor <thomas@stibor.net>\nChange-Id: I8c4cce5f861c9e4d01071024c4b852a2274c1b40\nReviewed-on: http://review.whamcloud.com/7913\nTested-by: Jenkins\nReviewed-by: Andreas Dilger <andreas.dilger@intel.com>\nTested-by: Maloo <hpdd-maloo@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Bob Glossman <bob.glossman@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Nathaniel Clark <nathaniel.l.clark@intel.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
